Two files to change:

1. docs/app/layout.tsx: Next.js 16 generates the viewport meta tag from the exported `metadata` or `viewport` config. Add a viewport export: `export const viewport = { themeColor: '#fff', viewportFit: 'cover' as const }`. This generates `<meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover'>`.

2. docs/app/global.css: Add safe-area-inset padding rules. Add to the body rule (line 150-152):
```css
body {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0px);
}
```
Add to #nd-global-header (create a new rule or modify existing):
```css
#nd-global-header {
  padding-left: max(1rem, env(safe-area-inset-left, 1rem));
  padding-right: max(1rem, env(safe-area-inset-right, 1rem));
}
```
This ensures the header px-4 (1rem) is the minimum, but expands for notched devices. The `max()` function ensures we never go below the existing 1rem padding.
